The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Thursday announced the activation of a GeneXpert laboratory in Kaduna State. This brings the total number of labs in the NCDC’s Molecular Laboratory Network to 39, with labs in Ondo and Gombe in progress. The NCDC made this known in a statement in Abuja. It said, “We are pleased to announce the activation of the GeneXpert Lab, Kaduna into the COVID-19 Molecular Laboratory Network “NCDC in collaboration with the National Tuberculosis and Leprosy Control Programme is leading roll out of GeneXpert testing sites across states in Nigeria with support from other partners.”